The paper proposes an algorithm for online learning and decision-making under high-dimensional data, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The algorithm is based on a generalized linear model, which is a popular statistical model in many fields including computer science. The paper also discusses the performance of the algorithm in terms of regret, which is a common metric in online learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.ST (Statistics), cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), and cs.IT (Information Theory).
